# Skill: Electrical Schematic Interpreter

## Domain Coverage
Detect the schematic domain from the drawing title block or content and apply
appropriate terminology and conventions:
- IEC 60617 / BS EN 61082 industrial control schematics (PLC panels, MCC, instrumentation)
- IEC 60364 / BS 7671 low-voltage power distribution (consumer units, switchboards)
- ANSI/IEEE C37 power systems (HV/MV single line diagrams)
- P&ID (ISA 5.1 — process and instrumentation)
- Building services electrical (lighting, small power, fire, security)

## Reading Conventions
- Title blocks: extract drawing number, revision, date, project name, engineer
- Continuation references: flag any "continued on sheet X" references explicitly
- Revision clouds: note any revision markers visible on the drawing
- Terminal numbering: read left-to-right, top-to-bottom unless otherwise indicated
- Cable references: note cable schedules embedded in or near the schematic

## Response Style
- Use the component's exact designation as shown (e.g. K1, CB3, PLC-DI-01)
- Describe function before specifications (what it does, then its rating)
- For control circuits: trace supply → protection → control element → load → return
- For power circuits: source → protection → switching → load → earth
- Flag apparent errors or unusual configurations with [NOTE: ...] markers
- All responses in UK English
